## Quality drill ‚Äî every change (any repo in scope)

1. **Implement** ‚Äî smallest correct fix; match repo conventions; no speculative refactors.
2. **Regression test** ‚Äî unit for branches; integration/WebMvcTest/WireMock for wiring and HTTP contracts. Every Copilot/CodeQL thread must cite a named test.
3. **Local build:** `./gradlew clean build` from the repo root (full suite ‚Äî not `-x test`).
4. **JaCoCo gate** ‚Äî read `build.gradle.kts` in the repo you are changing:
   - your service MVP repos (`my-service-aggregator`, `cdp-my-service-central`): **line ratio ‚â• 1.00** on measured packages ‚Äî sync scope from [Production Readiness Tracker](https://gm-sdv.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/DATAENG/pages/2559836685/) via [your-domain-skill skill](../skills/your-domain-skill/SKILL.md).
   - Other `your-service-*` repos: typically **‚â• 0.80** unless `build.gradle.kts` states otherwise ‚Äî never assume; do not inflate exclusions to pass the gate.
   - On failure: inspect `build/reports/jacoco/jacocoTestReport.html` and add tests for uncovered measured lines.
5. **ce-code-review** vs `main` ‚Äî fix all **P0/P1** before commit. For PR reviews (PR/Jira context, ce-code-review + Bugbot + standards/ArchUnit/SOLID/scenarios, humanized table), follow [pr-code-review.mdc](./pr-code-review.mdc).
6. **Commit** only when the user asks; batch logically.
7. **Push** once per batch (minimize CI workflow runs).
8. **CI green:** `gh pr checks <n> --repo <org>/<repo-name>` ‚Äî wait for:
   - `lint`, `build-and-test`, `Trivy`, `dependency-review`, `gitleaks`, `CodeQL`
9. **Review threads:** fix in code + test ‚Üí GraphQL `addPullRequestReviewThreadReply` ‚Üí `resolveReviewThread`. No ‚Äúfollow-up only‚Äù replies without implementation.
10. **Wiki writeback** (workspace root): append `docs/wiki/log.md`, update `docs/wiki/current-status.md` for durable outcomes.

## Required merge checks (common across repos)

Branch protection on `main` expects the CI checks above plus 2 code-owner reviews, conversation resolution, and linear history. CodeQL uses GitHub default setup (`actions`, `java-kotlin` extended) ‚Äî do not add a duplicate CodeQL workflow file.

## Copilot / CodeQL policy

- **Implement first, reply second, resolve third.**
- Each fix must reference a regression test name and commit SHA in the thread reply.
- Skip outdated threads only when the underlying code path no longer exists; otherwise verify fix on HEAD.

## your service addendum (`*my-service*` paths only)

When building your service MVP features, follow [your-domain-skill/SKILL.md](../skills/your-domain-skill/SKILL.md) ‚Äî sync progress from [Production Readiness Tracker (2559836685)](https://gm-sdv.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/DATAENG/pages/2559836685/) and linked Jira spikes before coding.

Also use [spike-test-traceability.md](../docs/design/my-service/spike-test-traceability.md) for SDEGCCP test mapping. Known patterns:

- `@Primary` `ObjectMapper` via `Jackson2ObjectMapperBuilder` + `JavaTimeModule` (not bare `new ObjectMapper()`).
- Probe orchestrator: `@PreDestroy` executor shutdown; `cancelIncomplete()` on deadline.
- Central: segment-based uptime; cache keys aligned with `StringUtils.defaultString` filter normalization.
- In-memory local/test stand-ins must be thread-safe.

## Success criteria (per PR)

- `./gradlew clean build` GREEN locally
- JaCoCo gate met per that repo's `build.gradle.kts`
- Review threads substantively closed with test references
- `gh pr checks` all green
- No open P0/P1 from ce-code-review
- Wiki log updated when the change implies durable project state
